				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: need some soloable shoulders<a name="7684"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 29 03 7:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>What I did for each of the hunters was chant them down.  Mana sieving the casters dry does work, but I find that incredibly tedious.  What I did was just put on all my resist gear, lulled each mob then single pulled and chanted them down.  My resists were roughly 100 in all and I didn't have any problems resisting the majority of their spells.  I did have a few problems with the wizard, but every time you see him start casting just get out of range real quick then go back in.  All in all they are pretty easy fights.  Oh a warning, the warrior mob will gate when low on health.  This is problematic if the cleric is still up as he will heal the warrior, so kill the cleric first.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
