				<td colspan="2"><span>I just completed the Draconic Pauldrons with the help of one of my guilds high level druids.  I have no real details on the battles as when I expressed my interest in the pauldrons we made arrangements to go get them the next morning and by the time I got on he had killed three of them leaving only the warrior, *caugh*joke*caugh*, which made me quite happy as I would have more instant gratification.
<br />

<br />
NOT...
<br />

<br />
First you need High Kindly or Warmly faction to do the turnin.  I was currently high amiable and with the faction song could only get to low/mid kindly, so off I went in search of faction.  I did this a few ways:
<br />

<br />
1. Mercenaries in EW and WL.  You gather their broaches and turn them into the same guy you get the pauldrons from.  Nice thing about this is you get decent faction and potions of Draconic Rage which are just uber fun to play with if you don't have procing weapons, proc is a fire based 65hp DD instant cast and won't interrupt your singing<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
2. Go into Kael and either get a group or see if you can tag others mobs.  I actually ran into someone that was getting pl'd so there were lots of pulls, eventually a few others showed up that wanted CoV faction and we headed off to the Arena.  I would not suggest tagging giants in GD as the faction you get from Kael is so much better.
<br />

<br />
Anyhow, I have my pauldrons and some potions.  Sooo much fun with max dex and deftdance<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
